Introduction
An Intelligent Route Planner is a system that finds the best route between two locations.

It uses graph algorithms to calculate the shortest path and total distance.

Applications:
• Google Maps
• Uber
• Ola
• Zomato
• Swiggy
• Logistics Companies



Objective
1. Create city map
2. Store locations as nodes
3. Store roads as edges
4. Apply BFS and DFS
5. Apply Dijkstra Algorithm
6. Find shortest route
7. Calculate total distance
8. Generate route report
